{{Infobox protected area | name = Georgian Bay Littoral | alt_name = | iucn_category = | photo =Georgian Bay Littoral trees (2).jpg | photo_alt = | photo_caption =Trees on rocky islands are typical of the area | photo_width = | map = Canada Ontario | map_alt = | map_caption = Location in Ontario | map_width = | relief = 1 | location = | nearest_city = | coordinates = {{coords|45|26|16|N|80|18|28|W|region:CA-ON_type:landmark_dim:100km|display=inline, title}} | area = {{convert|347270|ha}} | established = {{Start date|2004|11|2}} | visitation_num = | visitation_year = | governing_body = | world_heritage_site = | url = http://www.gbbr.ca }} [[File:BIOSPHERE-MAP-8x11 Mitig-2011.pdf|thumb|Map of the biosphere reserve]]
The '''Georgian Bay Littoral''' (also called the '''Georgian Bay Biosphere Reserve''') is a [[UNESCO]] [[Biosphere Reserve]] located in [[Ontario]], Canada. The biosphere was the thirteenth in Canada, and covers the [[Thirty Thousand Islands]] area of eastern [[Georgian Bay]],<ref name="UNESCO">{{cite web|url=http://www.unesco.org/mabdb/br/brdir/directory/biores.asp?mode=all&code=CAN+13|title=GEORGIAN BAY LITTORAL|work=UNESCO - MAB Biosphere Reserves Directory|publisher=UNESCO|archiveurl=https://www.webcitation.org/5uXEVTGCW?url=http://www.unesco.org/mabdb/br/brdir/directory/biores.asp?mode=all&code=CAN%2013|archivedate=26 November 2010|deadurl=yes|df=}}</ref><ref name="GC">{{cite press release|title=MINISTER DION WELCOMES THE DESIGNATION OF CANADA'S 13TH BIOSPHERE RESERVE|publisher=Government of Canada|date=4 November 2004|url=http://news.gc.ca/web/article-eng.do?crtr.sj1D=&mthd=advSrch&crtr.mnthndVl=1&nid=107039&crtr.dpt1D=&crtr.tp1D=&crtr.lc1D=&crtr.yrStrtVl=2004&crtr.kw=unesco&crtr.dyStrtVl=26&crtr.aud1D=&crtr.mnthStrtVl=2&crtr.yrndVl=2008&crtr.dyndVl=28|archivedate=26 November 2010|archiveurl=https://www.webcitation.org/5uXEdOTRZ?url=http://news.gc.ca/web/article-eng.do?crtr.sj1D=&mthd=advSrch&crtr.mnthndVl=1&nid=107039&crtr.dpt1D=&crtr.tp1D=&crtr.lc1D=&crtr.yrStrtVl=2004&crtr.kw=unesco&crtr.dyStrtVl=26&crtr.aud1D=&crtr.mnthStrtVl=2&crtr.yrndVl=2008&crtr.dyndVl=28|deadurl=yes|df=}}</ref> one of the world's largest [[fresh water]] [[archipelago]]s.<ref>{{cite press release |title=UNESCO Protects 19 New Biosphere Reserves |publisher=Environment New Service |date=2 November 2004 |url=http://www.ens-newswire.com/ens/nov2004/2004-11-02-04.html |archivedate=26 November 2010 |archiveurl=https://www.webcitation.org/5uXEwzaeB?url=http://www.ens-newswire.com/ens/nov2004/2004-11-02-04.html |deadurl=yes |df= }}</ref>
