The '''Indricotherium Formation''' is a [[paleontology|palaeontological]] formation located in [[Kazakhstan]]. It dates to the [[Oligocene]] period.
It is named after ''[[Paraceratherium]]'', also commonly known as ''Indricotherium'', an [[extinction|extinct]] [[genus]] of gigantic hornless [[rhinoceros]]-like mammals of the family [[Hyracodontidae]].
