==References== In order of likely publication:
*'''PNH''': [[Pliny the Elder|Pliny]] (Gaius Plinius Secundus), ''[[Pliny's Natural History|Naturalis Historia]]''; book "PNH" chapter (that is, "37PNH81" instead of the usual "N.H.xxxvii.81"). *'''PG''': [[Ptolemy]] (Claudius Ptolemaeus), ''[[Ptolemy#Geography|Geographia]]''; book "PG" chapter (that is, "2PG3" instead of the usual "II.3"). Ptolemy wrote in [[Greek language|Greek]], so names are [[transliteration|transliterated]] back into [[Latin]] to reveal the original form. *'''HLU''': [[Hofmann, Johann Jacob]] (1635–1706): ''Lexicon Universale'' *'''GOL''': The standard reference to Latin placenames, with their modern equivalents, is [[Johann Georg Theodor Grässe|Dr. J. G. Th. Grässe]], ''[[Orbis Latinus|Orbis Latinus: Lexikon lateinischer geographischer Namen des Mittelalters und der Neuzeit]]'' (1861), an exhaustive work of meticulous German scholarship that is available on-line in the second edition of 1909. To use it, one must understand German names of countries, as they were in 1909. The original was re-edited and expanded in a multi-volume edition in 1972.
